    "type": "message",
    "text": "Been loving these bookclub episodes.  Thoughts...\n• Can (and have) people visualized a Game Boy's by \"simply\" mapping its internal state entirely to the screen?  And by \"simply\" I mean \"not at all simply.\"  Then from there it would be fun to trace, for example, what goes into lighting up a given pixel or, going the other way, how a button press influences the game.\n• Multimedia vs metamedia?\n• Non-affine animation <https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H1MU7i3UzVQ>.\n• The :open_mouth: of learning that the Circle of Fifths is a hack <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pythagorean_comma>.",
